cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper proposes using a deep Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to predict the genre of a book based on its cover, which involves image processing and pattern recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions using machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper presents a new dataset, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
